cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.HC, cs.SY, cs.AR

This paper deals with the security risks and practical relevance of hardware Trojan insertion, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also involves reverse-engineering of proprietary firmware and hardware, which could be categorized under software engineering (cs.SE). The targeted USB flash drive is a high-security device, which could be related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The manipulation of the FPGA bitstream and ARM CPU code involves system-level design and implementation, which could be categorized under systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper involves the modification of hardware, which could be related to architecture (cs.AR).
